cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

This paper deals with the problem of resource allocation and interference control in a wireless network with D2D communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization and information theory concepts, which suggest that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with system-level design and control, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of fading channels, which could suggest a connection to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with practical implementation issues, which could place it in cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
